sentences.english: Tinned food is the least wasted.
sentences.chinese: 罐頭食品則是浪費最少的。

sentences.english: Superman has provided a chance to his girl of being a canning bride.
sentences.chinese: 超人已向他的姑娘提供了一個成爲罐頭業新娘的機會。

sentences.english: You may open the tin simply by pulling the puller.
sentences.chinese: 你只要拉這個拉出器，就可以很容易地把罐頭打開。

sentences.english: Clear amniotic fluid coated the can of cinnamon rolls.
sentences.chinese: 蛋清流到了裝肉桂卷的罐頭上。

sentences.english: Would it possible for me to see Mr. Wu, Manager of Canned Goods Department?
sentences.chinese: 我可以見一下罐頭部的經理，吳先生嗎？

sentences.english: He dug into the can and measured out a small spoonful of the powder .
sentences.chinese: 他伸手到罐頭裏舀出一小調羹白粉。

sentences.english: The utility model provides an easily opened cover for bottled can, and the utility model has a novel structure.
sentences.chinese: 本實用新型推出了一種結構新穎的瓶裝罐頭易開蓋。

sentences.english: The fish is canned in the factory.
sentences.chinese: 魚在這家廠裏裝成罐頭。

sentences.english: According to the properties of Jinshuai Apple, ways to solve the browning of canned food products are explored.
sentences.chinese: 據金帥蘋果的特性，探索解決罐頭褐變的途徑。

sentences.english: The cook served out tins of food to all the mountaineers.
sentences.chinese: 炊事員把罐頭食品分給所有登山隊員。
“罐頭魚”，一隻海上的怪物被解放了。

sentences.english: The invention relates to a canned seasoning garlic sprout and a preparation method thereof.
sentences.chinese: 本發明涉及一種調味蒜薹罐頭及其製備方法。

sentences.english: Many kitchens have a cookie jar for that purpose.
sentences.chinese: 因此許多家裏的廚房會有曲奇罐頭。

sentences.english: They recycle empty tins so as to use the metal.
sentences.chinese: 他們回收空罐頭盒以利用其金屬。
